
  <sn><md>### Soil Texture

Soil texture refers to the `relative proportion of primary soil particles`—**sand, silt and clay**—present in a soil sample. It describes the **feel**, **behavior**, and **physical properties** of soil. Texture strongly influences water holding capacity, aeration, permeability, fertility and root penetration.
Soils are classified texturally based on the percentages of sand, silt and clay.
